Lucky Charms Rice Krispie Treats 🍀🌈🍀🌈

Melt 4 T of butter then add a bag of mini marshmallows, stirring constantly.  Mix in 3 cups of Rice Krispies cereal followed by 3 cups of Lucky Charms until it’s all mixed together.  Grease a brownie pan or line with parchment paper and pour in the mixture, pressing down to make it even.  Add more Lucky Charms marshmallows on top if you want then let cool for an hour before cutting.  Enjoy!

You have to make these peach BBQ glazed meatballs that are perfect for spring and summer! 

I’m pairing them with a delicious @texashillcountrywine from Stonewall @abastriswinery . Did you know there are more than 50 unique wineries and scattered throughout the hill country?? So many to try. This is the time to make a plan to visit the Texas Hill Country! ad.

Recipe:
Combine 1 lb ground beef or pork, 1 egg, 3/4 cup breadcrumbs or Panko, crushed garlic, salt & pepper, splash of milk.  Form meatballs and line them on parchment paper. Cook at 400 for 15-20 minutes.  For sauce, combine @saltlickbbq spicy sauce and @fischerandwieser peach preserves. Heat in sauce pan and coat meatballs in sauce.  Enjoy!

Ever since last Father’s Day when we knew it was the last, I’ve been avoiding, and then as it crept up on me, dreading this day.  There have been many waves of grief that have come on fast and strong these last couple days as I think about this day, this summer, the vacations and trips, oysters and beach sunsets all without my dad. Finding some comfort in being grateful that he taught us how to enjoy life and we will carry that on. Whatever happens after this life, I hope he knows how much I miss him.

Happy National Tequila Day! Justin loves tequila, so I had to have him join me for this one. We made Hatch chile margaritas with @tequilareydelmundo blanco. We first discovered the premium sipping tequila at Austin Food + Wine fest last year and it’s delicious! ad

Hatch Chile Margarita:
Bring 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water to a boil with one chile and a few peppercorns. Muddle a few pieces of chile in a shaker then add 2 oz of the simple syrup, 2 shots tequila, fresh lime juice and shake. Add chili salt to the rim of your glass, pour and cheers!

Cranberry Barbecue Meatballs for #MeatballMonday

1 lb ground beef
1 lb ground pork
1 cup breadcrumbs
2 eggs
garlic powder, salt, pepper
splash of milk or water for extra moisture

Mix and form meatballs, line on parchment paper. Bake at 400 for 15 minutes before adding to crockpot. 

For the sauce:
1 jar of @bourbonbarrelfoods Barbecue sauce
1 jar of @lowcountryproduce Cranberry Pepper Jelly 
Both from @shophearthandsoul 

Cook on low for 4 hours or high for 2 hours. Enjoy!
